OL,3,CWhat does the two-child benefit cap
OL,4,Cbeing scrapped mean for the Midlands?
OL,6,FThe government has scrapped the two-
OL,7,Fchild benefit cap in one of the most
OL,8,Fhigh-profile decisions of this year's
OL,9,FBudget, but what does that mean for
OL,10,Fthe Midlands?
OL,12,FThe West Midlands has the highest rate
OL,13,Fof child poverty in the country at
OL,14,F38.5%, according to figures from the
OL,15,FJoseph Rowntree Foundation, and in the
OL,16,FEast Midlands it is almost 30%.
OL,18,FIn cities like Birmingham and
OL,19,FNottingham, some wards have child
OL,20,Fpoverty rates at more than 60%.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/14
