OL,3,CWhat does the two-child benefit cap
OL,4,Cbeing scrapped mean for the Midlands?
OL,6,FWhat was the two-child benefit cap?
OL,8,FDespite the name, the cap had nothing
OL,9,Fto do with the child benefit. It was
OL,10,Finstead related to Universal Credit.
OL,12,FIt's a restriction that meant parents
OL,13,Fcould only claim Universal Credit or
OL,14,Ftax credits for their first two
OL,15,Fchildren.
OL,17,FThose tax credits are equivalent to
OL,18,Faround #3,455 per child, according to
OL,19,Fthe Institute for Fiscal Studies (IFS).
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/14
