OL,3,CWhat does the two-child benefit cap
OL,4,Cbeing scrapped mean for the Midlands?
OL,6,FThe cap applied to any subsequent
OL,7,Fchild born after 6 April, 2017. It
OL,8,Fdidn't apply to multiple births like
OL,9,Ftwins or children born as a result of
OL,10,Frape or a coercive relationship.
OL,12,FExceptions were also made for children
OL,13,Fwho were adopted.
OL,15,FHow is poverty defined?
OL,17,FA child is considered to be living in
OL,18,Fpoverty if they are in a household
OL,19,Fwith an income below 60% of the
OL,20,Fcontemporary median income, after
OL,21,Fhousing costs.
