OL,3,CWhat does the two-child benefit cap
OL,4,Cbeing scrapped mean for the Midlands?
OL,6,FIn 2025, that is equivalent to around
OL,7,F#20,500 after the cost of your rent or
OL,8,Fmortgage.
OL,10,FHow will this affect the Midlands?
OL,12,FCampaign groups say this change will
OL,13,Fslash child poverty rates almost
OL,14,Fimmediately.
OL,16,FThe West Midlands is the only region
OL,17,Fthat has seen child poverty increase
OL,18,Fyear-on-year since the mid-1990s.
