OL,3,CWhat does the two-child benefit cap
OL,4,Cbeing scrapped mean for the Midlands?
OL,6,FBirmingham, for example, has seen one
OL,7,Fof the sharpest rises in child poverty
OL,8,Fof any city in the country. In the
OL,9,Flast 10 years, more than 30,000 more
OL,10,Fchildren have been living in poverty
OL,11,Fin the city.
OL,13,FWhile it is supercharged in some
OL,14,FMidlands cities, rising child poverty
OL,15,Frates can be seen across the country.
OL,16,FThe government says 700,000 more
OL,17,Fchildren are living in poverty now
OL,18,Fthan in 2010.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/14
