OL,3,CWhat does the two-child benefit cap
OL,4,Cbeing scrapped mean for the Midlands?
OL,6,FThe government has not given an
OL,7,Festimation on the number of children
OL,8,Fthat will be helped out of poverty in
OL,9,Feach region, now that the cap has been
OL,10,Fscrapped.
OL,12,FHowever, the Child Poverty Action
OL,13,FGroup say 350,000 children could be
OL,14,Fpulled out of poverty, and 700,000
OL,15,Fchildren will be in less deep poverty.
OL,17,FIn just the ten most affected areas of
OL,18,Fthe West Midlands, almost 30,000
OL,19,Fchildren will now be getting more
OL,20,Fbenefits as a result of this change.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/14
