OL,3,CWhat does the two-child benefit cap
OL,4,Cbeing scrapped mean for the Midlands?
OL,6,FResearch suggests this might not only
OL,7,Fbe good news for families but also for
OL,8,Fpublic services.
OL,10,FAccording to the University of
OL,11,FLiverpool, reducing rates of child
OL,12,Fpoverty will mean fewer children will
OL,13,Fenter care, there will be fewer infant
OL,14,Fdeaths and childhood hospital
OL,15,Fadmissions.
OL,17,FBut it was noted by the IFS that there
OL,18,Fhas been no correlation between the
OL,19,Ftwo-child benefit cap and any
OL,20,Fsignificant effect on the educational
OL,21,Foutcomes of children affected by it.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/14
