OL,3,CWhat does the two-child benefit cap
OL,4,Cbeing scrapped mean for the Midlands?
OL,6,FThe scrapping will also provide a cash
OL,7,Finjection into the poorest communities.
OL,9,FChild poverty is directly linked to
OL,10,Foverall poverty and deprivation.
OL,12,FCampaign group End Child Poverty
OL,13,Fsuggests that this benefit change
OL,14,Fwon't only help the families who get
OL,15,Fit but also the local economy.
OL,17,FTheir research suggests this change
OL,18,Fwill put more than #300 million into
OL,19,Fthe pockets of some of the poorest
OL,20,Fpeople in the West Midlands.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G9/14
